The launch of ‘Happy Birthday’ took place last Saturday at the All Saints Cathedral. The book explores the roles played by Mau Mau heroes and revolves around the struggle for Independence, hopelessness, unemployment, heroism and personal discipline. The book is authored by Njuguna Kimunya. Among those who attended the launch were authors Muthoni Likimani, Prof Godwin Siundu who is also University of Nairobi literature lecturer and columnist and writer Tee Ngugi.